From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Charles Kerr <charles@charleskerr.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 17:12:29 -0500
Subject: fix: preserve node symbols and vtables under thinlto

Clang's -fwhole-program-vtables (enabled with ThinLTO) drops
linkonce_odr vtables it considers unused. Several classes here have
all-inline virtuals and so have no key function, leaving their vtables
weak. Under ThinLTO the optimizer drops them, producing undefined
vtable symbols at link time. Anchor each vtable by moving one virtual
out-of-line:

  - StaticExternalByteResource (node_builtins.cc)
  - NgRcBufPointer<T>::External (node_http2.cc)
  - MemoryRetainerNode          (env.cc)
  - JSGraphJSNode               (heap_utils.cc)

Also mark N-API entry points with __attribute__((used)) so ThinLTO
does not strip them when no Node.js source references them directly,
following https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/49037 .

Observed on macOS arm64 official builds; latent on Linux/Windows.

diff --git a/src/env.cc b/src/env.cc
index 79a309661aff7ebb18f96e64d0d2b860ab80dc57..10266fd1233d9b117eefbbbb4f455289b002785a 100644
--- a/src/env.cc
+++ b/src/env.cc
@@ -2266,4 +2266,8 @@ v8::CpuProfile* Environment::StopCpuProfile(v8::ProfilerId profile_id) {
   return profile;
 }
 
+const char* MemoryRetainerNode::Name() {
+  return name_;
+}
+
 }  // namespace node
